---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Waybar from '../components/Waybar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import WindowChrome from '../components/WindowChrome.astro';
import BackToHome from '../components/BackToHome.astro';
import VimStatusline from '../components/VimStatusline.astro';

const workspaces = [
  { n: '1', name: 'Default' },
  { n: '2', name: 'Nord' },
  { n: '3', name: 'Gruvbox' },
  { n: '4', name: 'Dracula' },
  { n: '5', name: 'High Contrast' },
];

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const tokenReferenceUrl = `${base}tokens`;
---

<Layout title="Colophon — Nirmal">
  <Waybar />

  <main id="main-content">
  <article class="colo-page grid-bg">
    <div class="colo-inner">
      <header class="colo-header">
        <div class="back-home-row"><BackToHome /></div>
        <h1 class="colo-h1">Colophon</h1>
        <p class="colo-sub">How this site is put together — the stack, the system, and the lines I drew.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="colo-window vim-window">
        <WindowChrome title="colophon.md" activeTitle="[+]" icon="UTF-8">
          <div class="colo-window-body vim-window-body">
            <div class="colo-body">
              <h2>Stack &amp; why</h2>
              <p>
                This site runs on <strong>Astro and TypeScript</strong>. I chose it on purpose (and a bit of habit - I despise using React
                where it's not needed, this is mostly a static site and I shouldn't be using a reactive framework for mere buttons and dropdowns). 
                Astro ships static HTML by default and only sends JavaScript where needed, so the pages
                stay fast and the interactive bits: the workspace switcher, the jargon tooltips — load as small
                islands rather than dragging a whole framework along with them. For a portfolio, where most of the
                job is reading.
              </p>
              <p>
                It's deployed on Cloudflare Workers, with a GitHub Pages build path kept alongside it for me to stage changes.
              </p>

              <h2>Design tokens &amp; the five workspaces</h2>
              <p>
                The colour schemes you can switch between in workspaces 1 to 5 are not five separate themes bolted
                together. They are one set of design tokens with five palettes mapped onto the same variables. Type
                scale, spacing, and component styles all read from those tokens, so a single change propagates
                everywhere and nothing drifts out of sync. It is the same discipline I bring to product work: decide
                the system once, then let the screens inherit it.
              </p>

              <div class="swatch-grid">
                {workspaces.map((ws) => (
                  <div class="swatch-card" data-theme={ws.n}>
                    <div class="swatch-preview">
                      <div class="swatch-chip swatch-bg"></div>
                      <div class="swatch-chip swatch-bg1"></div>
                      <div class="swatch-chip swatch-bg2"></div>
                      <div class="swatch-chip swatch-lime"></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="swatch-meta">
                      <span class="swatch-num">{ws.n}</span>
                      <span class="swatch-name">{ws.name}</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
              <p class="swatch-note">
                Swatches are rendered live from the same <code>--bg</code>, <code>--bg1</code>, <code>--bg2</code>,
                and <code>--lime</code> custom properties the rest of the site uses, shown here in each theme's dark
                variant.
                <a href={tokenReferenceUrl}>See the full token reference →</a>
              </p>

              <h2>Performance &amp; accessibility budget</h2>
              <p>A few constraints I set before building, and kept:</p>
              <ul class="colo-list">
                <li>Semantic HTML first, JavaScript only where it earns its place.</li>
                <li>Every interactive element works by keyboard, not just mouse.</li>
                <li>Motion respects <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>. </li>
                <li>Contrast holds up across all five palettes, not just the one I happened to prefer while designing (it's Gruvbox, btw).</li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                A portfolio that writes mentions accessibility extensively should pass its own test. This site is meant to be the 
                proof of the proverbial pudding and there's an (AI-generated) accessibility test report linked in the footer.
              </p>

              <h2>What I chose not to build</h2>
              <p>
              There's no analytics, nobody's being watched as they scroll. While I'd love to hear from you, that has to be a voluntary decision 
              and this is not a product which I'm trying to optimise. With Claude Code being available, the tougher call has been choosing not to build,
              to not include a full desktop environment, or a calculator, or a mini browser where you can google things. All genuine ideas I thought of while 
              working on this site. I like to think that I bring this instict to everything I design: not designing for the sake of.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <VimStatusline filename="colophon.md" />
        </WindowChrome>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .colo-page {
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
  }

  .colo-inner {
    max-width: 880px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .colo-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .back-home-row {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .colo-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--lime);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .colo-sub {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--sub);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .colo-window {
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    scroll-snap-align: center;
  }

  .colo-window :global(.window) {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    height: calc(100vh - var(--bar-h) - 2rem);
    position: sticky;
    top: calc(var(--bar-h) + 1rem);
  }

  .colo-window-body {
    background: var(--bg1);
    padding: 2rem 1.75rem;
    overflow-y: hidden;
    flex: 1;
    min-height: 0;
  }

  .colo-body {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--sub);
    line-height: 1.75;
    animation: colo-fade-in 0.18s ease-out;
  }

  @keyframes colo-fade-in {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(4px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .colo-body { animation: none; }
  }

  .colo-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .colo-body h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .colo-body p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .colo-body strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .colo-body code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--lime);
    background: var(--lime-dim);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .colo-body a {
    color: var(--lime);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(158,255,87,0.35);
  }

  .colo-body a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--lime);
  }

  .colo-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .colo-list li {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .colo-list li::before {
    content: '›';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--lime);
  }

  .colo-todo {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--dim);
  }

  /* Token swatches */
  .swatch-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .swatch-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-hi);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--bg1);
  }

  .swatch-preview {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr;
    height: 72px;
  }

  .swatch-chip {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .swatch-bg { background: var(--bg); }
  .swatch-bg1 { background: var(--bg1); }
  .swatch-bg2 { background: var(--bg2); }
  .swatch-lime { background: var(--lime); }

  .swatch-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.7rem;
    background: var(--bg1);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .swatch-num {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--lime);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .swatch-name {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .swatch-note {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .colo-page { padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem; }
    .colo-window { height: auto !important; }
    .colo-window :global(.window) { height: auto; position: static; }
    .colo-window-body { overflow-y: visible; flex: none; }
    .swatch-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .colo-page { padding: 1.75rem 0.75rem; }
    .swatch-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
</style>

<script>
  import { initVimWindow } from '../lib/vim-window';
  initVimWindow();
</script>
